<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79352109-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s713a–11a"><num value="713a–11a">§ 713a–11a.</num><heading> Interest prohibited when reimbursing Corporation for net realized losses</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">After <date date="1964-09-30">September 30, 1964</date>, the portion of borrowings from Treasury equal to the unreimbursed realized losses recorded on the books of the Commodity Credit Corporation after September 30 of the fiscal year in which such losses are realized, shall not bear interest and interest shall not be accrued or paid thereon.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7935210a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/316/tIII/s301">Pub. L. 89–316, title III, § 301</ref>, <date date="1965-11-02">Nov. 2, 1965</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/79/1178">79 Stat. 1178</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/94/273/s2/6">Pub. L. 94–273, § 2(6)</ref>, <date date="1976-04-21">Apr. 21, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/375">90 Stat. 375</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7935210b-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
